First print out the list of options
establish the balance
Then establish a variable to hold the user's input
open a loop that will continue asking for input unless the user chooses the quit option.

for option 1 make a variable to hold the balance and print the value.

for option 2 ask user to input the amount to add. then add it to the original balance and display it.

for option 3 ask user how much to take away from the balance. If the amount is too high display "insufficient funds"
if it is not too high subtract the number and display the current balance.
